quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  73,1,"O you wrapped in garments (i.e. Prophet Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)!"
  73,2,"Stand (to pray) all night, except a little -"
  73,3,"Half of it or a little less than that,"
  73,4,"Or a little more. And recite the Qur’ân (aloud) in a slow, (pleasant tone and) style.{1}",footnotes:1:1
  73,5,"Verily, We shall send down to you a weighty Word (i.e. obligations, laws)."
  73,6,"Verily, the rising by night (for Tahajjud prayer) is very hard and most potent and good for governing oneself, and most suitable for (understanding) the Word (of Allâh)."
  73,7,"Verily, there is for you by day prolonged occupation with ordinary duties."
  73,8,"And remember the Name of your Lord and devote yourself to Him with a complete devotion."
  73,9,"(He Alone is) the Lord of the east and the west; Lâ ilâha illâ Huwa (none has the right to be worshipped but He). So take Him Alone as Wakîl (Disposer of your affairs).{1}",footnotes:1:1
  73,10,"And be patient (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) with what they say, and keep away from them in a good way."